Cheers to you, London 🇬🇧🍻 heres a recap ➡️

I had such an incredible time in London. The people were brilliant, the food was a lot better than I was led to believe, and the overall vibe was just fabulous. 

The first pic was taken at a bar called the Madison and it was overlooking St. Paul’s Cathedral which you can see from the video going up the elevator. The ABBA Voyage show was spectacular and I cried like 3 times during it because it was just so touching. I did some shopping, sight seeing, and even ate a waffle shaped like a pecker 🤣🥵 would do it all again 100/10. 

I have so much to share about it and I will be putting together more info from the trip eventually, but all I want to say right now is thank you for being here. I am so happy to have you in my life ❤️

Mark your calendars because I’m finally dropping my merch on 03/31/23 at 11am EST 😍❤️🥰 WOOHOO!!!

As some of you know, this has been a long time in the making. I’ve either gotten distracted or overwhelmed trying to make everything perfect. But I’ve learned that it’s okay to just go for it, and not everything has to be perfect (like the fact I never hired a professional photographer to take pics of me 😅) BUT ITS OK!!!! There are bound to be mistakes in anything we do, but we learn from those mistakes and just do better each time. Life will go on 🫶 

I’ll be making a reel & sharing content over the next week or so explaining the merch and my thoughts behind it, but there was a lot of time and love put into every single piece. I wanted something that was cozy but good quality. I wanted you to have a little reminder that you are worthy of good things, better things, AND ONLY THE BEST OF THINGS 🥹💕 and most importantly I wanted you to feel like you had your bestie there to comfort you at any time. Again, I’ll be posting more about each piece, but wanted to get this out there to show you IT IS HERE!!!! Woooo!!!!

Thank you so much for the love you give and the support you have shown. I’m overwhelmed by your kindness and I’m so grateful you are here existing with us. Thank you for giving me the opportunity to be myself. 

As for the offerings, there will be t-shirts, hoodies, and crewnecks (in sizes S thru 3X) as well as a cute keychains. All in similar styling!

(P.S. yes we will be shipping internationally!!!)

(P.P.S There will be limited quantities because I’ve had to fulfill these orders with my own money, so please don’t be mad at me when we sell out 😭)

After 7+ years together, me and my husband are callin it quits. I’ve been processing this for a bit now but thought it was time to share. This is why I’ve been a bit absent. 

We are ending on friendly terms, so its been a lot less heated than one would expect after being together this long. Idk what the next chapter holds, but I hope it’s one that makes us both happy.

I have decided to share this part of my life because I could really use the support. And I want to take you along my new journey. Thank you for being here with me.
Just wanted to check in and let you know I’m doing ok. And I appreciate you so very much.

One day I hope I can love again, but right now it seems impossible. All that said, I wouldn’t be able to do this without you. I can’t thank you enough for the support and kindness you’ve shown me. I truly appreciate you so much. Breakups are hard, but I’m learning that we can get through anything together. Happier content is to come, I know it. I see a light at the end of the horizon and I’m looking forward to better things… for all of us.

Well, after this breakup its time to learn how to love myself more!!! I’m ready to step out of my comfort zone and try new things. I’ll be posting here a lot more, so watch out hehe. I appreciate all the support and love you give me.
Thank you for being so incredible.
Reminding myself that there’s joy in taking myself out on dates! It’s been so nice just connecting with me & my own existence. I feel like I’m never alone because I always have you.

I’m starting to see myself again and it’s so nice. Now I’m working on melding the new version of me with parts of the old me. I’m feeling more motivated to do content. More motivated to be who I truly am. More motivated to share my love. It’s incredible. I’m so thankful you’re here.

I took a chance, met some wonderful people, and explored a whole new country. Spain, you were incredible. And the company was top tier 😘😍

If you’ve been following along for a bit now, you know I’ve made travel a priority in my healing journey. Doing things like this has been such a great benefit for me. 

My message to you is DO IT! Whatever you are afraid of doing, I want you to sprint head first into it. Don’t over think. Don’t hold yourself back. You can do incredible things, my love 🥰💋 time to take a chance on YOU!

Lemme say that all of these pictures are just a small glimpse into the smiles, laughs, and fun that we had in Madrid ❤️💛

Trying to make new traditions for myself. Which is harder said than done, but I’m learning everyday! I decided to take a cruise with some friends and I do not regret it. I felt selfish at first bc I wasn’t spending the l holiday with my family, but I realized that I really needed to take care of me in this moment. So lucky that my family is understanding and supportive of me 🥹❤️

I will say I have been struggling with being drained in large social settings so I’m stepping out of my comfort zone and putting myself out there anyways. It’s been a process, but I’m so thankful for people in my life who aren’t afraid to speak up when they notice I’m “off.”

All of that said, cheers to you and I hope you have a great holiday, my love. You are incredible!!! Never forget it 😍
